<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910125-0015</DOCNO><DOCID>910125-0015.</DOCID><HL>   Stevens Graphics Sets   Charge in 4th Quarter   Totaling $5 Million</HL><DATE>01/25/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   SVGA</CO><IN>FACTORY EQUIPMENT (FAC)EARNINGS (ERN)</IN><LP>   FORT WORTH, Texas -- Stevens Graphics Corp. said it willtake a $5 million charge in its fourth quarter for closingsome facilities, reducing its workforce and putting someassets up for sale.   The maker of printing presses said last month that itexpects to report an operating loss for the fourth quarter,largely because of a six-week strike at its Hamilton, Ohio,manufacturing plant.</LP><TEXT>   Paul I. Stevens, chairman and chief executive officer,declined to elaborate on the company's plans becauseemployees haven't been informed. He said plant closings andother changes will be disclosed &quot;sometime after the first ofMarch.&quot;   The changes in operations are intended to bring thecompany's costs in line with its orders, which are down about30% compared to a year ago, Mr. Stevens said.   In the fourth quarter of 1989, Stevens had net income of$3.7 million, or 46 cents a share, on sales of $37.6 million.</TEXT></DOC>